WEBVTT

00:00.050 --> 00:35.875
Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org

01:09.125 --> 01:12.083
[flames crackling]

01:18.542 --> 01:21.333
-[flames whooshing]
-[baby crying]

01:26.083 --> 01:28.583
[distant screams]

01:32.333 --> 01:34.708
[fire roaring]

01:36.125 --> 01:37.792
[man screaming]

01:54.000 --> 01:57.375
[keyboard clacking]

02:03.542 --> 02:05.000
[Caitlin] I'm sorry. Okay. Keep going.

02:07.125 --> 02:08.917
Well, then things got really bad.

02:09.833 --> 02:12.708
The family that I was nannying for,
they had to move.

02:12.792 --> 02:14.917
[Caitlin] And that's what you do?
You're in child care?

02:15.000 --> 02:17.667
Yeah. Well, that's what I love.

02:17.750 --> 02:21.625
Um, I was going to school for it.
Uh, early education.

02:21.708 --> 02:23.833
But then, you know, losing this job,

02:23.917 --> 02:25.583
uh, it's just really hard financially.

02:25.667 --> 02:27.125
Yeah, for sure.

02:27.208 --> 02:29.292
But then I get this email
from my landlord saying,

02:29.375 --> 02:31.208
"We're raising your rent. Good day."

02:31.292 --> 02:32.583
I'm glad you came today.

02:33.542 --> 02:37.083
You know, cases like yours are
exactly why my firm does these events.

02:41.125 --> 02:44.708
So, this is what you do?
Pick fights with landlords?

02:44.792 --> 02:48.708
My firm handles all kinds of housing
and real estate issues.

02:50.042 --> 02:52.625
Keeping landlords honest, we do that...

02:52.708 --> 02:53.917
We do that pro bono.

02:55.958 --> 02:57.958
-It's like a perk.
-[cell phone buzzing]

02:59.167 --> 03:00.417
Um...

03:07.042 --> 03:08.458
So, what are you doing here?

03:09.542 --> 03:11.042
[chuckles]
What do you mean?

03:11.875 --> 03:13.083
You're about to pop.

03:13.750 --> 03:17.500
Shouldn't you be home
drinking raspberry tea?

03:18.333 --> 03:22.500
Well, that sounds very nice,
but, um, I'm managing.

03:23.750 --> 03:24.750
People do it.

03:25.708 --> 03:26.875
[chuckles]

03:27.875 --> 03:31.125
-[door creaks]
-[siren wailing in distance]

03:32.583 --> 03:36.042
[man] LA Law. There she goes.

03:36.125 --> 03:37.125
[Caitlin] Hi, Henry.

03:43.333 --> 03:47.875
[woman] Please, Daddy.
I promise that Mama's home. I promise.

03:53.208 --> 03:54.625
[phone line ringing]

03:55.625 --> 03:57.958
- [Alison over phone] Hi, Caitlin.
-Hey, Alison.

03:58.042 --> 04:00.417
Um, where's the contract? I need it.

04:01.417 --> 04:03.042
He says he's still proofreading.

04:03.625 --> 04:04.833
I can call him again.

04:06.375 --> 04:07.500
Uh...

04:08.250 --> 04:10.750
I-I think we're gonna
have to pick this up later.

04:10.833 --> 04:13.125
- [breathes deeply]
-Oh. Is everything okay?

04:13.208 --> 04:15.458
Uh, yeah. Um...

04:15.542 --> 04:17.208
Yeah, I just think I'm going into labor.

04:17.292 --> 04:18.500
-Oh.
-[breathes deeply]

04:27.917 --> 04:30.042
Just tell me. How are they not real?

04:30.125 --> 04:32.542
-Where are my keys?
-Mom?

04:32.625 --> 04:35.125
-Earth to Mom.
-Can you hold this a second?

04:36.042 --> 04:37.042
Mom.

04:37.125 --> 04:38.875
-What, the baby animals?
-Yeah.

04:38.958 --> 04:41.083
-Because they're in a video game.
-It costs money.

04:41.167 --> 04:42.875
Why would they cost money
if they're not real?

04:42.958 --> 04:44.542
Yeah, that's exactly my question.

04:50.167 --> 04:52.750
-[gate creaks]
-Let's make some space.

04:52.833 --> 04:54.208
Mom, this is serious to me.

04:54.292 --> 04:55.667
I know, honey. I know.

04:55.750 --> 04:57.750
I know.
You're saying it's serious to you.

04:57.833 --> 04:59.250
And I get it. But we need to go.

04:59.333 --> 05:01.833
-Can you get in the car?
-I'm helping.

05:01.917 --> 05:04.917
[grunts] Okay. There we go.

05:08.125 --> 05:09.333
[vehicle approaching]

05:09.417 --> 05:10.625
[tires screech]

05:10.708 --> 05:13.208
-What are you doing?
-[woman] What are you doing?

05:13.292 --> 05:14.792
You leave your baby
in the street?

05:14.875 --> 05:17.250
[Caitlin] You can't just
drive down here that fast.

05:17.333 --> 05:19.542
[woman] Oh, you're lucky that stroller
didn't damage my car.

05:19.625 --> 05:21.292
-[Caitlin] Come on.
-[woman] Dumb bitch.

05:21.375 --> 05:23.125
[engine revs]

05:24.417 --> 05:26.667
-Oh, come on.
-[Miguel roars]

05:26.750 --> 05:29.750
-Are we ready to do this?
-[Emma] Dad.

05:29.833 --> 05:31.667
-[Caitlin] Jesus.
-[Miguel] What the hell?

05:32.500 --> 05:34.292
-What happened?
-[Caitlin] This woman...

05:34.375 --> 05:36.833
She just came speeding down here.

05:36.917 --> 05:38.875
-What a fucking idiot.
-[Emma] Dad.

05:38.958 --> 05:42.333
What? If it's true, you can say "fuck."

05:42.458 --> 05:43.917
[Josie fussing]

05:44.000 --> 05:45.583
There should be a stop sign there.

05:45.667 --> 05:48.500
-Yeah, well, LA.
-[Caitlin] What does that mean?

05:49.042 --> 05:50.958
-People don't stop in LA.
-Oh...

05:54.167 --> 05:55.792
No, there should be a stop sign.

05:59.000 --> 06:00.000
Thank you.

06:01.250 --> 06:03.167
Okay. Tomatoes...

06:07.250 --> 06:08.875
Okay, we're not buying those today.

06:09.458 --> 06:11.792
Let's check out the apples over there.

06:13.042 --> 06:14.208
Hmm.

06:22.375 --> 06:23.417
Caitlin.

06:27.833 --> 06:30.042
-Polly. Yeah.
-Polly. Right.

06:30.125 --> 06:31.500
Wow. How are you?

06:32.042 --> 06:33.667
I'm good. Yeah, I'm good.

06:34.333 --> 06:36.083
What happened with your landlord?

06:36.167 --> 06:38.083
Um, I sent him a letter,

06:38.167 --> 06:40.667
but he said something about, you know,
the law with rent increase,

06:40.750 --> 06:42.333
that unfortunately it doesn't apply.

06:42.417 --> 06:44.125
Well, he's wrong.

06:44.208 --> 06:46.292
-What you need to do is--
-It's fine.

06:46.375 --> 06:48.333
You know, I'm-I'm getting by.

06:49.250 --> 06:50.250
[Miguel] Got pesto.

06:51.875 --> 06:55.083
Um, yeah, it has palm oil.

06:56.125 --> 06:57.125
Is that bad?

06:57.750 --> 07:01.292
-Well, it's 50% saturated fat, so...
-[chuckles]

07:01.375 --> 07:03.292
[Miguel] I thought fat was
a good thing now.

07:03.375 --> 07:06.083
It... There's different kinds.
Can you take it back?

07:06.167 --> 07:08.250
Sure. I just thought, for pasta, it'd...

07:08.333 --> 07:10.167
-[Josie fussing]
-[Emma] Mom.

07:10.250 --> 07:13.250
-So, what's your plan, then, as far as...
-Mom? Mom.

07:13.333 --> 07:15.000
I'm speaking, Emma, okay?

07:15.083 --> 07:17.250
-[Emma] Can we go now?
-We just got here.

07:17.333 --> 07:20.375
-I'm hungry. Mom.
-We're gonna get food, okay?

07:20.458 --> 07:21.583
Um...

07:22.500 --> 07:27.250
If you ever needed a babysitter,
even just for an afternoon

07:27.333 --> 07:31.167
to really, you know,
nail the farmers' market...

07:31.250 --> 07:34.583
-And you're in childcare?
-I am. Um...

07:34.667 --> 07:38.042
I had mentioned it, you know,
but that was a long time ago. [laughs]

07:38.125 --> 07:39.375
I remember, yeah.

07:40.917 --> 07:42.750
Let me see if I have your number.

07:42.833 --> 07:43.833
Okay.

07:44.750 --> 07:46.792
[Caitlin] I mean,
she's had a rough go of it.

07:48.208 --> 07:53.958
It's just easier to talk to her than,
like, half the moms at Emma's school.

07:54.042 --> 07:56.542
She's just like an actual person.

07:57.750 --> 08:00.500
But she has experience with kids?

08:00.583 --> 08:02.792
Yeah. Yeah, I'll get a reference from her.

08:03.750 --> 08:07.083
-Mom, not too short.
-[Caitlin] I know. There you go.

08:07.167 --> 08:09.125
-And you said you wanted a break.
-[Caitlin] I do.

08:09.208 --> 08:13.667
I could... I could go a bit easier
this time, and, um...

08:14.250 --> 08:16.667
take care of myself,
like everybody's always demanding.

08:20.375 --> 08:21.542
Okay.

08:24.208 --> 08:25.208
Okay.

08:30.417 --> 08:31.417
Right.

08:32.917 --> 08:34.583
What do you think?

08:36.750 --> 08:38.750
-[Emma] Perfect.
-[exclaims softly]

08:39.750 --> 08:40.750
Gold star.

08:40.833 --> 08:42.875
Ooh. Why, thank you.

08:47.500 --> 08:49.250
[line ringing]

08:52.333 --> 08:54.625
- [Rosanna] Hello.
-Hi, Rosanna?

08:55.333 --> 08:58.000
-Uh, yes.
-Hi. My name's Caitlin.

08:58.083 --> 09:01.042
I... I got your number from Polly Murphy.

09:01.125 --> 09:04.083
-Oh. Hi.
-Hi. Yeah.

09:04.167 --> 09:06.208
We're considering hiring her as a nanny

09:06.292 --> 09:09.708
and I was just curious
about your experience with her.

09:09.792 --> 09:11.250
Oh, um...

09:12.042 --> 09:14.292
[stutters] She's amazing.

09:14.375 --> 09:16.208
Really became a part of our family.

09:16.292 --> 09:18.083
-That's great to hear.
-[Josie crying]

09:18.167 --> 09:20.792
Sorry. [stutters] How long
did she work for you?

09:22.542 --> 09:26.125
-Gosh, a couple of years.
-Uh-huh.

09:26.208 --> 09:28.125
Okay. Wow. That's great.

09:28.208 --> 09:30.625
That's a... That's a really long time.
[shushes]

09:30.708 --> 09:35.250
-Yeah. Really wonderful with the kids.
- [Josie fussing]

09:36.625 --> 09:38.375
[gate creaking]

09:46.292 --> 09:47.292
Hi.

09:50.333 --> 09:53.458
So, clean go here, and then
dirties straight in the dishwasher.

09:53.542 --> 09:55.667
-There's a sterilized cycle.
-Okay.

09:56.208 --> 09:57.500
And just glass bottles.

09:58.125 --> 10:00.000
Right. Hold on the microplastics.

10:00.875 --> 10:05.958
Exactly. Yes, I know we're a lost cause,
but, you know, hopefully for them.

10:08.167 --> 10:10.000
Uh, okay. Here.

10:10.083 --> 10:13.208
-Oh, wow.
-Yeah, I've stocked up quite a lot.

10:13.292 --> 10:15.667
So we've got left to right,
older to newer.

10:15.750 --> 10:18.667
-So you can just pull from the left.
-And no formula?

10:18.750 --> 10:21.375
For... Oh. No, that stuff is just sugar.

10:21.458 --> 10:23.667
So once she has that... you know.

10:23.750 --> 10:25.542
-Got it. Yeah.
-Okay.

10:26.125 --> 10:27.208
Josie.

10:28.000 --> 10:29.708
Josie, it's your new nanny, Polly.

10:29.792 --> 10:31.083
-Want to say hi?
-Hi.

10:31.167 --> 10:32.167
Hi.

10:34.917 --> 10:36.417
Mommy says no sugar.

10:36.500 --> 10:37.542
[toy] Mommy says no sugar.

10:39.917 --> 10:41.292
[Polly] Hi, baby.

10:41.417 --> 10:43.208
- [toy] Hi baby.
- [gasps]

10:50.708 --> 10:52.250
[pills rattle]

11:18.292 --> 11:21.417
So, I think, um,
I'm gonna go run some errands.

11:21.500 --> 11:22.667
Great. Yeah.

11:25.625 --> 11:26.750
Um...

11:27.708 --> 11:29.792
-We'll be fine.
-Right. [chuckles nervously]

11:29.875 --> 11:30.917
[Josie chuckles]

11:31.625 --> 11:32.625
Okay.

11:34.375 --> 11:35.458
Bye.

11:43.333 --> 11:44.542
[door closes]

11:48.208 --> 11:52.792
♪ She talks to birds
She talks to angels ♪

11:52.875 --> 11:56.625
♪ She talks to trees
She talks to bees ♪

11:56.708 --> 11:59.125
♪ She don't talk to me ♪

11:59.208 --> 12:03.333
♪ Talks to the rainbows
and to the seas... ♪

12:04.250 --> 12:05.833
[music fades]

12:17.625 --> 12:20.167
[dog barking in distance]

12:31.708 --> 12:33.292
-[engine revving]
-Jesus!

12:37.208 --> 12:38.292
[scoffs]

12:41.292 --> 12:43.500
-[Miguel] Hello.
-Hello.

12:43.583 --> 12:45.667
-Food's here.
-Great.

12:51.042 --> 12:53.542
-Josie's asleep, so I'm gonna head home.
-Great. Okay.

12:53.625 --> 12:55.375
Uh, do you want dinner?

12:55.458 --> 12:57.375
-Yeah.
-I mean, there's plenty.

12:58.458 --> 12:59.542
Please, stay.

13:01.417 --> 13:03.667
-Stay.
-Okay. [chuckles softly]

13:03.750 --> 13:05.250
[Emma] I'll go get another plate.

13:06.000 --> 13:07.333
[Caitlin] Here you go.

13:07.417 --> 13:08.542
Oh, I don't drink.

13:09.500 --> 13:12.583
Cool. Um, my love.

13:13.458 --> 13:15.833
Great. Thank you. Okay.

13:16.917 --> 13:19.083
All right. This looks good.

13:19.167 --> 13:22.000
-[Miguel] Emma, you want the chicken?
-Have whatever you want, just dig in.

13:22.083 --> 13:23.333
Okay.

13:24.083 --> 13:26.458
[indistinct conversation]

13:30.417 --> 13:31.500
I need space!

13:31.583 --> 13:33.167
-Emma...
-[door slams]

13:33.250 --> 13:35.625
You can have space,
but you cannot speak to me in that...

13:35.708 --> 13:37.250
[Emma] My God! Leave me alone!

13:38.375 --> 13:39.417
[sighs]

13:39.542 --> 13:41.292
Should you just give her a second?

13:43.375 --> 13:46.042
[clicks tongue] Yeah. [clears throat]

13:46.917 --> 13:50.042
She thinks I'm this controlling,
like, scold.

13:50.708 --> 13:53.500
It's 'cause all the other parents
are scared of their own kids.

13:53.583 --> 13:54.875
I see that a lot.

13:56.208 --> 14:00.167
Emma's smart, but she is super willful.

14:00.250 --> 14:03.250
Ever since she was a baby,
if I set her down even for one second,

14:03.333 --> 14:05.083
she would just scream.

14:05.167 --> 14:08.000
-Scream.
-[Polly] Sounds so hard.

14:12.333 --> 14:15.875
Yeah, that first year was,
um, was something.

14:18.833 --> 14:21.042
[cell phone buzzing]

14:21.958 --> 14:24.208
Hey, you know what?
Don't let me keep you. Really.

14:24.292 --> 14:27.000
-If you need to...
-Oh. No, it's just, um...

14:28.542 --> 14:29.667
this girl.

14:29.750 --> 14:31.375
We've been sort of talking.

14:32.458 --> 14:35.208
Oh, yeah? You like her?

14:36.750 --> 14:37.833
I'm not sure yet.

14:40.542 --> 14:41.583
It's, um...

14:42.167 --> 14:45.000
It's funny. I was dating a woman
when I met Miguel.

14:46.458 --> 14:47.875
I think I could tell that.

14:51.292 --> 14:52.542
Really?

14:52.625 --> 14:53.708
About me?

14:54.583 --> 14:57.333
Yeah. You have that vibe to you.

15:03.333 --> 15:05.833
-I think this is going back.
-I like it.

15:08.333 --> 15:09.417
Do you want it?

15:10.083 --> 15:12.292
I mean, maybe it looks better on you.

15:15.250 --> 15:16.333
Okay.

15:19.333 --> 15:20.333
Let's see.

15:21.083 --> 15:22.292
Oh, yeah.

15:26.333 --> 15:28.042
I'm sorry. Is that weird? I...

15:28.125 --> 15:31.000
No. No, I... I love it.

15:38.833 --> 15:40.750
You know what?
Um, I'll grab you some scissors.

15:40.833 --> 15:41.875
Cut the tag.

16:02.708 --> 16:04.667
-[door closes]
-[Miguel moans softly]

16:20.583 --> 16:21.625
[kisses]

16:22.625 --> 16:24.417
[kissing continues]

16:35.042 --> 16:36.333
Miguel, um,

16:37.292 --> 16:39.125
can we try tonight?

16:39.833 --> 16:41.833
Maybe? I'm just not... I'm not...

16:42.708 --> 16:44.250
[Miguel groans]

16:44.333 --> 16:46.458
-Right now.
-Okay.

16:48.958 --> 16:50.708
[sighs softly]

16:50.792 --> 16:54.125
I'm sorry. I've missed you, too, you know?

16:55.667 --> 16:57.875
I've missed you, too.
It's just Josie, and...

16:58.625 --> 16:59.750
It's fine.

17:00.250 --> 17:01.333
It's okay.

17:14.250 --> 17:18.333
Oh, you know what, I have that, um...
stop sign meeting this afternoon.

17:19.042 --> 17:20.125
[Miguel] Mm-hmm.

17:21.208 --> 17:23.333
Could you take Emma to basketball?

17:24.083 --> 17:26.167
I can't. I'm meeting with the builders.

17:27.583 --> 17:28.583
Okay.

17:29.958 --> 17:31.875
Why don't you ask Polly to take her?

17:31.958 --> 17:33.083
It's walking distance.

17:34.000 --> 17:35.042
Oh, yeah.

17:35.708 --> 17:36.708
Okay.

17:43.458 --> 17:45.000
I have a surprise for you.

17:50.208 --> 17:51.250
[gasps]

17:53.208 --> 17:55.458
-[Polly] Don't tell.
-I won't.

17:59.875 --> 18:02.875
Do you want some, Josie? I bet you do.

18:04.333 --> 18:06.333
Here. [gasps] Mm.

18:09.625 --> 18:10.750
Give her some.

18:12.750 --> 18:14.083
It's so much sugar.

18:14.208 --> 18:15.542
It's good for you.

18:24.167 --> 18:26.458
Mm. [laughs]

18:27.667 --> 18:29.167
Did your mom let you eat sugar?

18:29.250 --> 18:30.333
She did.

18:31.875 --> 18:33.250
She made the best cupcakes.

18:36.583 --> 18:39.042
But before I got too old,
she had to go away.

18:40.500 --> 18:42.042
But your dad could stay?

18:43.333 --> 18:44.417
Nope.

18:47.417 --> 18:48.667
The place I went to live,

18:49.417 --> 18:51.792
the only thing they had to eat
was tuna fish.

18:51.875 --> 18:54.375
-[chuckles] That's silly.
-It is.

18:55.542 --> 18:57.333
But it gets even sillier than that.

18:58.792 --> 19:01.583
There was no mayonnaise, no lettuce,

19:02.625 --> 19:03.750
no bread even.

19:06.000 --> 19:08.917
I had to eat the tuna
out of a can, like a cat.

19:10.750 --> 19:12.375
And when there was no more left...

19:18.250 --> 19:19.833
there was nothing left to eat.

19:22.500 --> 19:23.625
[Emma chuckles]

19:29.583 --> 19:32.000
[both shushing]

19:34.375 --> 19:37.792
Whoa! Whoo!

19:37.875 --> 19:39.167
Whee!

19:39.250 --> 19:41.625
Whoa! [chuckles]

19:42.375 --> 19:43.750
Oh, my goodness.

19:43.833 --> 19:46.250
Whoa. Wow.

19:47.375 --> 19:48.417
[chuckles]

19:49.083 --> 19:51.917
[Josie cooing]

20:02.667 --> 20:03.833
She's so beautiful.

20:10.417 --> 20:11.500
She is.

20:14.208 --> 20:16.250
[Josie cooing]

20:16.333 --> 20:17.417
[Polly] Ready?

20:25.958 --> 20:27.083
[alarm beeps]

20:27.167 --> 20:30.125
[automated voice] Emergency.
There's smoke in the kitchen.

20:30.208 --> 20:32.750
-Smoke alarm detected in the kitchen.
-Okay.

20:32.833 --> 20:34.542
[indistinct chatter on video]

20:36.667 --> 20:37.667
What are you making?

20:38.333 --> 20:39.833
Uh, cioppino.

20:40.708 --> 20:42.208
It's like a fish stew.

20:43.417 --> 20:44.458
Huh.

20:46.000 --> 20:47.083
Hey, I can cook.

20:47.875 --> 20:50.083
Okay? I'm cooking. I can cook.

20:51.125 --> 20:53.042
It's just Stewart coming, right?

20:53.125 --> 20:55.875
Uh, I think he's bringing Bethany.

20:57.000 --> 21:00.083
I mean, we could just get In-N-Out
and tacos or something.

21:00.167 --> 21:04.583
You can't invite people over to dinner
and then just get In-N-Out.

21:04.667 --> 21:06.625
-Come on.
-Oh, I think this is burning.

21:06.708 --> 21:08.958
-Okay. Shit.
-[Miguel] Oh, boy.

21:09.042 --> 21:11.750
Out of my kitchen. Out.
Everybody out of my kitchen.

21:11.833 --> 21:13.125
Okay, chapino.

21:13.208 --> 21:16.208
-Cioppino. We're getting banished.
-[Polly laughs]

21:22.000 --> 21:25.167
[Stewart] But that's assuming
that a police presence reduces crime.

21:25.250 --> 21:28.292
Or that it helps at all
at resolving disputes.

21:28.375 --> 21:31.833
I mean, there are studies
that show the opposite.

21:31.917 --> 21:33.167
-What studies?
